1
00:00:00,578 --> 00:00:06,714
♪

2
00:00:06,794 --> 00:00:07,916
[door creaking]

3
00:00:08,006 --> 00:00:09,047
[ALBERT] Huh.

4
00:00:09,718 --> 00:00:10,879
Welcome back, Theodora.

5
00:00:12,261 --> 00:00:14,053
I go by Esta now, Albert.

6
00:00:14,383 --> 00:00:15,384
Esta, right.

7
00:00:15,925 --> 00:00:17,226
Still getting used to that.

8
00:00:17,386 --> 00:00:24,394
♪

9
00:01:58,589 --> 00:01:59,630
♪

10
00:01:59,710 --> 00:02:01,252
[ALBERT] The former
demon lord's airship?

11
00:02:01,792 --> 00:02:03,504
That's correct,
the very same vessel

12
00:02:03,594 --> 00:02:04,846
Ruti took to Zoltan.

13
00:02:05,847 --> 00:02:08,390
Should Van be granted clearance
to into the territory

14
00:02:08,970 --> 00:02:11,603
and should he by chance run
into to Ruti while he's there,

15
00:02:11,804 --> 00:02:13,435
I fear what would happen next.

16
00:02:13,896 --> 00:02:16,399
Under no circumstances
can their paths cross.

17
00:02:16,519 --> 00:02:17,520
Hmm.

18
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:20,613
Therefore, I ask you head
to Zoltan in my place.

19
00:02:21,064 --> 00:02:23,116
Red must be informed
of these events.

20
00:02:23,697 --> 00:02:24,698
You can count on me.

21
00:02:25,909 --> 00:02:28,872
This new hero.
You think he's the real deal?

22
00:02:29,323 --> 00:02:30,324
Mmm.

23
00:02:31,285 --> 00:02:32,877
He was appraised by the saint.

24
00:02:33,127 --> 00:02:35,460
Leadership from the Church
have recognized him, too.

25
00:02:36,381 --> 00:02:38,173
So I would surmise
that he must be.

26
00:02:39,334 --> 00:02:40,796
But he is nothing like Ruti.

27
00:02:42,468 --> 00:02:45,091
All we can do is wait,
and see what becomes of him.

28
00:02:45,841 --> 00:02:46,842
Then we wait.

29
00:02:47,013 --> 00:02:48,144
Leave it to me, Esta.

30
00:02:48,514 --> 00:02:50,096
I'll do whatever I can to help.

31
00:02:50,597 --> 00:02:51,598
[chuckles]

32
00:02:52,809 --> 00:02:53,810
[ESTA] Thank you, Albert.

33
00:02:54,901 --> 00:02:56,153
I'm glad you're here with me.

34
00:02:58,315 --> 00:03:02,320
♪

35
00:03:02,490 --> 00:03:03,571
[door opens]

36
00:03:04,532 --> 00:03:05,573
Good morning, Nao.

37
00:03:05,864 --> 00:03:07,115
Good day to you, Red!

38
00:03:07,205 --> 00:03:09,578
I'll take some of your
newest concoction, please!

39
00:03:09,828 --> 00:03:11,670
The dragonshroom essence,
you mean?

40
00:03:11,790 --> 00:03:12,791
That's the one!

41
00:03:12,921 --> 00:03:15,544
One sip and I feel
on top of the world!

42
00:03:15,795 --> 00:03:16,836
One sip, huh?

43
00:03:17,256 --> 00:03:20,300
It's not every day you swing
by the shop this early, Nao.

44
00:03:20,590 --> 00:03:22,722
Gotta be ready
to go for the festival!

45
00:03:22,802 --> 00:03:24,094
If I waste time,
the day will slip

46
00:03:24,184 --> 00:03:25,515
right by before I know it!

47
00:03:25,726 --> 00:03:26,727
[chuckles]

48
00:03:27,267 --> 00:03:29,310
I'll throw in an extra
for Mido and Gonz.

49
00:03:30,020 --> 00:03:31,062
[NAO] Thanks, Red!

50
00:03:32,063 --> 00:03:36,528
♪

51
00:03:36,608 --> 00:03:37,779
All. Set.

52
00:03:38,820 --> 00:03:40,322
[RED] Rit! Time to go!

53
00:03:41,323 --> 00:03:42,324
[RIT] Coming!

54
00:03:43,826 --> 00:03:44,907
[chuckles]

55
00:03:45,077 --> 00:03:49,162
♪

56
00:03:49,332 --> 00:03:52,005
Thanks for waiting!
How do I look?

57
00:03:52,756 --> 00:03:54,508
Great!
The cape is a nice touch.

58
00:03:55,299 --> 00:03:57,841
You look rather handsome
yourself in that coat!

59
00:03:59,804 --> 00:04:01,095
You ready for the festival?

60
00:04:01,475 --> 00:04:04,058
[chuckles] And what about
that one order from Zeff?

61
00:04:04,809 --> 00:04:06,141
All packed. Right here.

62
00:04:06,731 --> 00:04:08,023
Great! Let's go!

63
00:04:08,683 --> 00:04:11,687
[indistinct chatter]

64
00:04:13,529 --> 00:04:16,612
Wow. Everyone is so festive!

65
00:04:17,744 --> 00:04:18,785
Today's the Drake Rider

66
00:04:18,865 --> 00:04:21,037
and Saint Licinius's
Solstice Festival,

67
00:04:21,618 --> 00:04:23,330
based on an Avalonian legend.

68
00:04:24,621 --> 00:04:26,914
Even the famously
laid-back people of Zoltan

69
00:04:27,004 --> 00:04:29,667
are out living it up
from sun-up to sundown.

70
00:04:30,588 --> 00:04:32,960
[GONZ] Aye! Red!
[BOTH] Hmm?

71
00:04:34,302 --> 00:04:35,343
[gurgling]

72
00:04:35,804 --> 00:04:37,516
Wild party, huh?

73
00:04:37,806 --> 00:04:39,558
[RED] Not sure
about that, Gonz.

74
00:04:39,968 --> 00:04:41,100
Lively energy though!

75
00:04:41,350 --> 00:04:42,721
Yeah, because I'm here!

76
00:04:42,811 --> 00:04:45,605
Today is all about enjoying
the day off at the festival!

77
00:04:45,725 --> 00:04:46,776
[laughs]

78
00:04:46,976 --> 00:04:49,148
[gulping]

79
00:04:49,819 --> 00:04:51,071
[Gonz laughs]

80
00:04:51,231 --> 00:04:53,573
[GONZ] Tomorrow's about
sleeping off the hangover!

81
00:04:53,734 --> 00:04:55,736
You're taking today
and tomorrow off?

82
00:04:55,946 --> 00:04:57,237
[GONZ] Come on,
you gotta play hooky

83
00:04:57,328 --> 00:04:59,039
-the day after a party!
-[gasps]

84
00:04:59,410 --> 00:05:00,912
Yeah, you tell 'em, Gonz!

85
00:05:01,042 --> 00:05:02,243
The Ultimate Man!

86
00:05:02,373 --> 00:05:03,374
Ultimate?

87
00:05:03,875 --> 00:05:05,126
It's all downhill from here

88
00:05:05,206 --> 00:05:07,048
if I don't step in now,
as the adult.

89
00:05:07,339 --> 00:05:08,590
-[munching]
-[RED] Tanta.

90
00:05:08,710 --> 00:05:10,712
Can it wait 'til after I eat?

91
00:05:11,053 --> 00:05:13,636
Real men will be up bright
and early for work tomorrow!

92
00:05:13,806 --> 00:05:15,968
[TANTA] Boo, there's too much
to do today!

93
00:05:16,889 --> 00:05:18,221
-Like, look at that!
-[BOTH] Huh.

94
00:05:18,601 --> 00:05:21,605
[crowd cheering]

95
00:05:21,685 --> 00:05:23,607
♪

96
00:05:23,687 --> 00:05:25,018
[RIT] This is how
the Drake Rider

97
00:05:25,108 --> 00:05:26,730
and Saint Licinius's
Solstice Festival

98
00:05:26,820 --> 00:05:27,982
goes in Zoltan, huh?

99
00:05:28,402 --> 00:05:30,404
[TANTA] Is it different
where you're from, Rit?

100
00:05:31,115 --> 00:05:33,698
Way more formal
and stricter back in Loggervia.

101
00:05:34,279 --> 00:05:35,280
Formal how?

102
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:36,371
[Rit chuckles]

103
00:05:36,701 --> 00:05:37,993
[RIT]
The objective is the same.

104
00:05:38,453 --> 00:05:40,916
The Drake Rider and Saint repel
the winter demons.

105
00:05:42,167 --> 00:05:44,590
But it's great how each region
does it differently.

106
00:05:45,591 --> 00:05:47,133
[TANTA] Well,
here we sing, dance,

107
00:05:47,213 --> 00:05:48,795
and party like no tomorrow

108
00:05:48,885 --> 00:05:50,547
to chase
the winter demons away!

109
00:05:51,598 --> 00:05:53,100
It's the Zoltan way.

110
00:05:53,550 --> 00:05:54,852
[GONZ] It really does a number

111
00:05:54,932 --> 00:05:56,013
-on you.
-[all gasp]

112
00:05:56,143 --> 00:05:57,685
No choice but to get wasted

113
00:05:57,765 --> 00:06:00,057
and then sleep off
the crappy hangover!

114
00:06:00,398 --> 00:06:01,859
He may have a point.

115
00:06:02,310 --> 00:06:03,521
We do deserve a day off!

116
00:06:03,611 --> 00:06:05,523
-Huh. Come on, Rit.
-[noisemaker honking]

117
00:06:05,614 --> 00:06:07,115
[IN UNISON] Take the day off!

118
00:06:07,486 --> 00:06:08,907
Take the day off!

119
00:06:09,318 --> 00:06:10,699
Take the day off!

120
00:06:11,160 --> 00:06:12,531
Take the day off!

121
00:06:12,912 --> 00:06:14,073
-Take the day off!
-All right.

122
00:06:14,163 --> 00:06:15,454
-I understand.
-[gasps]

123
00:06:15,745 --> 00:06:18,328
Place will be a ghost town
by tomorrow anyway.

124
00:06:18,788 --> 00:06:20,710
No work then. Guess you win.

125
00:06:20,921 --> 00:06:23,503
[giggling] Yay!

126
00:06:24,044 --> 00:06:25,466
-[IN UNISON] Yay!
-[gasps]

127
00:06:25,886 --> 00:06:27,758
We want to take off, too.

128
00:06:28,219 --> 00:06:29,220
Um, "we"?

129
00:06:30,011 --> 00:06:30,892
Okay.

130
00:06:30,972 --> 00:06:32,303
[squeaking]

131
00:06:32,594 --> 00:06:34,476
[sighs]
Of course you guys do.

132
00:06:35,016 --> 00:06:38,190
First Tanta, and now Tisse
and Ruti have gone rogue on me.

133
00:06:38,560 --> 00:06:39,731
-Huh.
-You're enjoying this?

134
00:06:39,812 --> 00:06:40,813
[chuckles]

135
00:06:41,233 --> 00:06:42,354
A little bit.

136
00:06:42,525 --> 00:06:44,026
[giggles]

137
00:06:44,106 --> 00:06:47,070
♪

138
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:49,242
[Oparara grunting]

139
00:06:49,953 --> 00:06:52,165
Refreshing, wouldn't you say?

140
00:06:52,245 --> 00:06:54,037
As long as you're comfy.

141
00:06:54,368 --> 00:06:55,919
-[groaning]
-Everything okay?

142
00:06:56,460 --> 00:06:58,462
Are you ready to leave already,
Oparara?

143
00:06:58,833 --> 00:07:01,756
Like hell! If that's a joke,
it ain't funny, Megria!

144
00:07:01,876 --> 00:07:04,509
I'm just gettin' warmed up
is all, nothin' more!

145
00:07:05,220 --> 00:07:07,382
Warmed up? In that case!

146
00:07:08,133 --> 00:07:10,886
-[MEGRIA] Here.
-[screaming]

147
00:07:11,056 --> 00:07:13,099
[steam whistling]

148
00:07:13,309 --> 00:07:14,730
Hmm. Hmm.

149
00:07:14,981 --> 00:07:16,562
That smells great.

150
00:07:16,943 --> 00:07:19,946
[groaning]

151
00:07:21,278 --> 00:07:26,033
♪

152
00:07:26,323 --> 00:07:27,324
[sighs]

153
00:07:27,705 --> 00:07:29,247
Here you go, I got you a drink.

154
00:07:29,407 --> 00:07:30,538
Lifesaver!

155
00:07:31,079 --> 00:07:34,082
[both gulping]

156
00:07:34,753 --> 00:07:36,294
[BOTH] Aah!

157
00:07:37,085 --> 00:07:38,587
[RED] Day off
for you two as well?

158
00:07:38,917 --> 00:07:39,758
-Yep!
-[sighs]

159
00:07:39,838 --> 00:07:41,260
Adventurers' Guild is closed!

160
00:07:42,261 --> 00:07:43,633
Sounds mighty nice.

161
00:07:44,343 --> 00:07:45,725
Working the festival.

162
00:07:46,015 --> 00:07:48,558
Need to take the cart out
to feed folks, right?

163
00:07:48,728 --> 00:07:50,600
I figured while my oden's busy

164
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:52,643
gettin' real tasty stewing
and simmering

165
00:07:52,733 --> 00:07:54,775
in the pot
right about now... [inhales]

166
00:07:55,896 --> 00:07:56,937
I'd do the same.

167
00:07:57,238 --> 00:07:59,360
Came down to sweat it out
and detox.

168
00:07:59,490 --> 00:08:00,491
[TISSE] Smart!

169
00:08:00,862 --> 00:08:03,114
You can really bring out
the best flavors in oden

170
00:08:03,194 --> 00:08:04,536
depending on how long
it's simmered.

171
00:08:04,656 --> 00:08:05,617
-[squeaks]
-[WILLIAM] Hold it, you!

172
00:08:05,697 --> 00:08:07,789
[LEON] Let me go!
I didn't do anything!

173
00:08:07,870 --> 00:08:09,121
-[ALL] Hm?
-[WILLIAM] Hey!

174
00:08:09,581 --> 00:08:12,455
I know for a fact you saw me
standing right there, kid!

175
00:08:12,545 --> 00:08:15,047
I was here before you!
Quit cutting in line!

176
00:08:15,128 --> 00:08:16,459
-Seriously?
-[scoffs]

177
00:08:17,420 --> 00:08:19,012
-And what's going on here?
-[gasps]

178
00:08:19,512 --> 00:08:21,054
[WILLIAM] This kid cut in line.

179
00:08:21,635 --> 00:08:23,847
No! I was here first, you liar!

180
00:08:23,967 --> 00:08:25,850
You're just trying to get
in front of me!

181
00:08:25,930 --> 00:08:27,021
Oh, come on!

182
00:08:27,101 --> 00:08:29,433
I could step right over you
if I wanted, shrimp!

183
00:08:29,524 --> 00:08:30,975
Don't you dare mock me!

184
00:08:31,276 --> 00:08:33,068
[screams]

185
00:08:34,689 --> 00:08:36,401
-[gasps]
-Ugh.

186
00:08:36,732 --> 00:08:38,033
Huh. [gasps]

187
00:08:40,075 --> 00:08:42,578
-[LEON] Ademi.
-That sure would've been messy.

188
00:08:42,908 --> 00:08:43,910
Huh?

189
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:45,201
[gasps]

190
00:08:45,702 --> 00:08:48,084
[whimpers]

191
00:08:48,545 --> 00:08:50,587
[ADEMI] Forgive him
for losing his cool there, sir.

192
00:08:51,248 --> 00:08:52,249
[WILLIAM] Hm.

193
00:08:52,799 --> 00:08:53,801
The thing is,

194
00:08:54,051 --> 00:08:55,633
his Blessing awakened recently,

195
00:08:55,753 --> 00:08:57,174
so he's still a bit unstable.

196
00:08:57,465 --> 00:08:59,217
-[ADEMI] Now, apologize.
-[gasps]

197
00:08:59,927 --> 00:09:00,929
[LEON] I'm sorry!

198
00:09:01,639 --> 00:09:02,640
Don't be.

199
00:09:03,181 --> 00:09:05,013
I got a little carried away,
too.

200
00:09:05,894 --> 00:09:08,567
Can't blame a guy for his
Blessing's impulses, can I?

201
00:09:09,648 --> 00:09:11,981
[RED] "Can't be blamed for your
Blessing's impulses," huh?

202
00:09:14,484 --> 00:09:16,776
[RIT] Ademi's really grown up,
hasn't he?

203
00:09:17,487 --> 00:09:18,528
He sure has.

204
00:09:18,989 --> 00:09:20,280
[YARANDRALA] Red!
[BOTH] Huh?

205
00:09:20,620 --> 00:09:23,624
Everyone! [laughs]

206
00:09:23,744 --> 00:09:25,956
Who's that bouncy-yell-y person
over there?

207
00:09:26,167 --> 00:09:27,418
-[YARANDRALA] Hello!
-[gasps]

208
00:09:27,498 --> 00:09:28,589
[RED] Yarandrala!

209
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:29,961
-[RED] Over here!
-Hmm.

210
00:09:30,592 --> 00:09:31,593
[YARANDRALA] Rit!

211
00:09:32,253 --> 00:09:33,254
Huh.

212
00:09:33,345 --> 00:09:34,546
[laughs]

213
00:09:34,636 --> 00:09:36,718
The town's truly livened up
today!

214
00:09:37,099 --> 00:09:39,722
[Red laughs]
Glad to hear you're having fun!

215
00:09:39,892 --> 00:09:42,555
There are so many stalls set up
that I've never seen before!

216
00:09:42,975 --> 00:09:43,976
Behold!

217
00:09:44,107 --> 00:09:45,308
One said this sacred mask

218
00:09:45,398 --> 00:09:47,520
was made by
a legendary great sage!

219
00:09:47,650 --> 00:09:49,112
-[Yarandrala laughs]
-Just wondering,

220
00:09:49,192 --> 00:09:51,485
but exactly how old
are you, again?

221
00:09:51,565 --> 00:09:52,906
Huh? Huh.

222
00:09:53,817 --> 00:09:56,821
Some might say I'm a lass
of around 50 years young!

223
00:09:56,951 --> 00:09:59,033
-[laughs]
-Aw.

224
00:09:59,494 --> 00:10:00,955
That's an elf joke.

225
00:10:01,125 --> 00:10:06,081
♪

226
00:10:06,251 --> 00:10:08,003
Come one, come all! Huh.

227
00:10:08,133 --> 00:10:13,719
♪

228
00:10:14,260 --> 00:10:16,182
-[gasps]
-Hey, what's the deal, boss?

229
00:10:16,513 --> 00:10:17,894
When were you gonna tell me
you hang around

230
00:10:17,974 --> 00:10:19,146
a Kiramin elf, huh?

231
00:10:19,226 --> 00:10:20,687
-A Kiramin elf?
-Yeah.

232
00:10:20,938 --> 00:10:22,019
It's an elf thing.

233
00:10:22,519 --> 00:10:24,942
We refer to one another
by the land we were born in.

234
00:10:25,312 --> 00:10:27,064
So that makes me a Zoltan elf.

235
00:10:27,565 --> 00:10:29,487
I'm amazed that
you can tell where she's from.

236
00:10:30,068 --> 00:10:31,489
[OPARARA]
We just kinda know, okay?

237
00:10:31,740 --> 00:10:34,322
Even among high elves,
Kiramin are somethin' special.

238
00:10:34,743 --> 00:10:35,994
How do you expect
little old me,

239
00:10:36,074 --> 00:10:37,786
a country bumpkin
from the middle of nowhere,

240
00:10:37,866 --> 00:10:38,867
to talk to her?

241
00:10:39,368 --> 00:10:41,080
I'm sweatin' buckets over here!

242
00:10:42,081 --> 00:10:43,082
Oparara, was it?

243
00:10:43,423 --> 00:10:44,424
Uh. Yes, ma'am!

244
00:10:45,044 --> 00:10:46,716
[YARANDRALA]
While I do hail from Kiramin,

245
00:10:46,966 --> 00:10:48,008
don't let that discourage you

246
00:10:48,088 --> 00:10:49,970
from treating me
as you would anyone else.

247
00:10:50,180 --> 00:10:51,181
Huh?

248
00:10:51,471 --> 00:10:52,513
Act natural.

249
00:10:53,053 --> 00:10:55,436
Yarandrala's an old friend
of mine from way back,

250
00:10:56,137 --> 00:10:57,889
which makes us
all friends here.

251
00:10:59,731 --> 00:11:00,942
Yeah, I guess you're right!

252
00:11:01,272 --> 00:11:03,104
Since introductions
are out of the way,

253
00:11:03,315 --> 00:11:05,357
I am eager to taste
some hearty oden!

254
00:11:05,777 --> 00:11:08,030
Uh, well you've come
to the right place!

255
00:11:08,400 --> 00:11:09,782
So! What'll it be, then?

256
00:11:09,862 --> 00:11:11,824
How 'bout fresh octopus,
just in today?

257
00:11:11,954 --> 00:11:13,456
Or fish balls!

258
00:11:13,656 --> 00:11:15,118
I'll take an order of those.

259
00:11:15,708 --> 00:11:16,910
Add some burdock, too.

260
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:19,042
I'll take the octopus
with egg, please.

261
00:11:19,372 --> 00:11:21,625
You can make mine
the same as milady's dish.

262
00:11:21,965 --> 00:11:24,378
And four orders of grilled
fish paste too, please.

263
00:11:24,839 --> 00:11:27,221
And I think I'll have octopus,

264
00:11:27,301 --> 00:11:29,133
the burdock, egg with fish
and squid ball,

265
00:11:29,223 --> 00:11:30,675
beef tendon and radish.

266
00:11:31,096 --> 00:11:32,137
And what else?

267
00:11:32,347 --> 00:11:34,730
Throw in the fish cake,
seaweed, and jelly strings.

268
00:11:35,060 --> 00:11:36,271
Oh, plus a cake pouch!

269
00:11:36,351 --> 00:11:37,773
Did you add the whole menu?

270
00:11:37,933 --> 00:11:38,774
Huh?

271
00:11:38,854 --> 00:11:40,936
It all just sounded
so good, okay?

272
00:11:41,317 --> 00:11:42,568
And for you, Yarandrala?

273
00:11:43,189 --> 00:11:44,240
My turn next?

274
00:11:44,691 --> 00:11:46,322
Your order sounds lovely.

275
00:11:46,533 --> 00:11:48,285
Octopus and burdock for me.

276
00:11:48,575 --> 00:11:50,367
Add some fish balls, too,
please.

277
00:11:50,657 --> 00:11:52,579
Mm-hmm. Right away!

278
00:11:54,001 --> 00:11:55,002
[OPARARA] Order up!

279
00:11:55,833 --> 00:11:57,165
[IN UNISON] Let's eat!

280
00:11:57,835 --> 00:12:00,048
Add this here and it'll taste
twice as good!

281
00:12:01,589 --> 00:12:03,051
That's not a part of our order.

282
00:12:03,512 --> 00:12:04,553
It's too expensive!

283
00:12:04,963 --> 00:12:06,925
It's from the lady to my left.

284
00:12:07,596 --> 00:12:09,388
-You ordered this?
-Sure did.

285
00:12:10,269 --> 00:12:12,101
[RED] Wait, wait!
I'm the big brother here,

286
00:12:12,181 --> 00:12:13,853
I can't have you paying for us.

287
00:12:14,774 --> 00:12:17,858
You are talking to a hotshot
B-ranked adventurer.

288
00:12:18,278 --> 00:12:21,732
My bag is more than
a little heavy, as you can see.

289
00:12:21,942 --> 00:12:23,444
[RED] Is that
what I think it is?

290
00:12:23,944 --> 00:12:26,237
Wasn't it you who told me
to live as I wanted?

291
00:12:26,737 --> 00:12:27,739
Well, right now,

292
00:12:27,989 --> 00:12:30,792
I want my brother and friends
to enjoy some yummy oden.

293
00:12:31,413 --> 00:12:32,414
[chomps]

294
00:12:32,834 --> 00:12:34,336
No way that's all hers.

295
00:12:34,666 --> 00:12:36,088
-Step in, please.
-Hm?

296
00:12:36,799 --> 00:12:38,961
I completely agree
with milady's decision.

297
00:12:41,634 --> 00:12:42,635
Hmm.

298
00:12:42,885 --> 00:12:44,507
Ha. [chomps]

299
00:12:45,388 --> 00:12:46,509
Hmm.

300
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:51,185
♪

301
00:12:51,435 --> 00:12:53,858
All right. Thank you, Ruti

302
00:12:54,318 --> 00:12:55,319
[RUTI] Mhm.

303
00:12:57,612 --> 00:12:59,023
[IN UNISON] Mmm!

304
00:12:59,274 --> 00:13:01,326
[all laughing]

305
00:13:01,406 --> 00:13:03,078
-[RED] Mm.
-[RIT] Oh.

306
00:13:04,660 --> 00:13:07,703
♪

307
00:13:08,374 --> 00:13:11,337
[indistinct chatter]

308
00:13:11,667 --> 00:13:12,879
-[gasps]
-[YARANDRALA] Huh?

309
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:15,291
[Godwin groaning]

310
00:13:15,632 --> 00:13:17,754
Huh? Now, now. Come here!

311
00:13:17,924 --> 00:13:19,927
You are Zoltan's
representative, right?

312
00:13:20,798 --> 00:13:22,800
-[MISTROM] Act like it!
-[groans] Mercy!

313
00:13:22,970 --> 00:13:25,102
-[Godwin grunts]
-[YARANDRALA] A representative?

314
00:13:25,553 --> 00:13:26,894
We stopped
by the zoogs' village

315
00:13:26,974 --> 00:13:27,976
while gem-hunting,

316
00:13:28,266 --> 00:13:30,148
and learned from their elder
they were struggling

317
00:13:30,228 --> 00:13:31,399
due to a lack of trade.

318
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:32,561
Oh.

319
00:13:33,732 --> 00:13:35,904
[RED] Godwin will be
handling that from now on.

320
00:13:36,986 --> 00:13:39,408
Man, thanks for looking out
for your old pal.

321
00:13:39,659 --> 00:13:41,070
I owe ya big-time, Red!

322
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:43,122
You just keep an eye out
for any monsters

323
00:13:43,202 --> 00:13:44,284
that are on the way there.

324
00:13:44,624 --> 00:13:46,746
Are you sure
this guy can be trusted?

325
00:13:47,247 --> 00:13:49,710
What are you talking about?
Trust is my middle name!

326
00:13:49,790 --> 00:13:52,212
He's a piece of work,
but he's capable, at least.

327
00:13:52,333 --> 00:13:54,045
Put those skills of yours
to use.

328
00:13:54,175 --> 00:13:55,636
They're depending on you
to make amends.

329
00:13:55,716 --> 00:13:57,388
[chuckles] Huh?

330
00:13:57,929 --> 00:13:59,971
Well, looks like it's time
for the grand finale.

331
00:14:00,051 --> 00:14:01,092
Oh, let's see!

332
00:14:01,393 --> 00:14:04,847
♪

333
00:14:04,977 --> 00:14:07,650
[panting]

334
00:14:08,020 --> 00:14:11,314
[grunting] Come on!

335
00:14:11,774 --> 00:14:13,026
Follow the script!

336
00:14:13,356 --> 00:14:15,609
You're supposed to be
good and dead by now!

337
00:14:15,699 --> 00:14:16,820
[sobs]

338
00:14:17,030 --> 00:14:21,415
Huh. Is that you,
my beloved lady warrior?

339
00:14:21,705 --> 00:14:23,367
-Who's that?
-[RUTI] No idea.

340
00:14:23,577 --> 00:14:25,459
Move! You're blocking my view!

341
00:14:25,920 --> 00:14:27,792
-[Otto chuckles]
-He's staring right at you.

342
00:14:27,872 --> 00:14:30,425
[RUTI] Hmm?
[TISSE] Hmm?

343
00:14:31,046 --> 00:14:33,048
Isn't that the same guy
you threw off the bridge

344
00:14:33,128 --> 00:14:34,720
on the way to Zoltan, milady?

345
00:14:35,130 --> 00:14:37,223
-Oh!
-[OTTO] Huh!

346
00:14:38,554 --> 00:14:39,976
-Doesn't ring a bell.
-Oh!

347
00:14:41,187 --> 00:14:43,309
Otto is my name,
fair warrior-maiden!

348
00:14:43,690 --> 00:14:45,061
Please remember it! [gasps]

349
00:14:45,392 --> 00:14:46,393
Huh?

350
00:14:47,814 --> 00:14:49,947
[RED] Hold on.
That you, Danan?

351
00:14:52,029 --> 00:14:53,030
[thuds]

352
00:14:53,901 --> 00:14:55,112
Long time no see!

353
00:14:55,533 --> 00:14:57,745
-A very long time indeed!
-So.

354
00:14:58,116 --> 00:15:00,078
I hear you'll be staying
in Zoltan for a while.

355
00:15:00,248 --> 00:15:01,249
Huh?

356
00:15:01,540 --> 00:15:03,001
What happened to your arm?

357
00:15:03,372 --> 00:15:04,623
[DANAN] It's not a big deal.

358
00:15:04,713 --> 00:15:06,215
It looks like a big deal!

359
00:15:07,296 --> 00:15:08,297
Are you okay?

360
00:15:08,718 --> 00:15:09,799
[DANAN] I'm fine.

361
00:15:10,299 --> 00:15:12,592
If you ask me, it's not
the comeback I had in mind,

362
00:15:12,762 --> 00:15:15,385
but the doc kept nagging me
about taking it slow.

363
00:15:15,765 --> 00:15:17,137
[YARANDRALA] So much for that!

364
00:15:17,427 --> 00:15:19,059
[DANAN]
This counts as taking it slow.

365
00:15:19,139 --> 00:15:21,522
[Otto groans]

366
00:15:22,022 --> 00:15:24,185
[gasps]
Cursed winter demon!

367
00:15:24,485 --> 00:15:26,187
Show yourself, wretched fiend!

368
00:15:26,397 --> 00:15:29,320
Whoops. I guess that's my cue
to get back in there.

369
00:15:29,691 --> 00:15:36,699
♪

370
00:15:38,701 --> 00:15:40,873
[crowd cheering]

371
00:15:40,953 --> 00:15:43,046
[crowd applauding]

372
00:15:43,797 --> 00:15:50,804
♪

373
00:15:56,311 --> 00:15:59,024
[male villager 203A chuckles]
Man, I wish there was a way

374
00:15:59,104 --> 00:16:00,395
to make some easy coin.

375
00:16:00,896 --> 00:16:03,148
[WOLF] Hidden treasure
we could plunder, maybe.

376
00:16:03,438 --> 00:16:04,440
[MALE VILLAGER 203A] Right?

377
00:16:05,070 --> 00:16:08,324
[KAI] Now you're talking!
Say like, an airship?

378
00:16:08,574 --> 00:16:10,076
-Huh.
-Get outta here,

379
00:16:10,156 --> 00:16:11,367
keep dreaming, pal!

380
00:16:11,577 --> 00:16:12,579
Worth a shot.

381
00:16:12,659 --> 00:16:15,662
[all laughing]

382
00:16:17,244 --> 00:16:24,212
♪

383
00:16:32,010 --> 00:16:33,011
Hey, so.

384
00:16:33,812 --> 00:16:36,435
Thanks for today.
I had a good time.

385
00:16:36,976 --> 00:16:37,977
Hm?

386
00:16:38,477 --> 00:16:40,319
Me too. It was fun.

387
00:16:41,651 --> 00:16:42,652
[Ruti chuckles]

388
00:16:43,823 --> 00:16:46,116
[RED] But, there's still
one thing left to do.

389
00:16:46,366 --> 00:16:47,367
Huh?

390
00:16:47,828 --> 00:16:48,829
[Ruti chuckles]

391
00:16:50,030 --> 00:16:51,452
May I have this dance with you?

392
00:16:51,872 --> 00:16:54,415
Dance with you?
Are you sure about this?

393
00:16:56,207 --> 00:16:57,208
Hmm.

394
00:16:58,339 --> 00:17:00,502
Can't remember
the last time I danced.

395
00:17:01,133 --> 00:17:03,215
Maybe before your induction
to knighthood?

396
00:17:04,636 --> 00:17:06,178
I won't be the best partner.

397
00:17:06,679 --> 00:17:08,681
It's not about how good
you are at it.

398
00:17:09,392 --> 00:17:11,434
It's about having fun
and just dancing.

399
00:17:12,185 --> 00:17:13,186
Right?

400
00:17:14,517 --> 00:17:15,519
[RUTI] Hmm...

401
00:17:15,769 --> 00:17:17,941
♪

402
00:17:18,111 --> 00:17:19,113
Right.

403
00:17:19,273 --> 00:17:21,946
♪

404
00:17:22,116 --> 00:17:23,157
Is this okay?

405
00:17:23,948 --> 00:17:24,949
What is it?

406
00:17:25,910 --> 00:17:28,493
Am I really allowed
to feel such warmth?

407
00:17:29,034 --> 00:17:30,535
Can I be this happy?

408
00:17:32,497 --> 00:17:33,829
Of course you can, Ruti.

409
00:17:34,580 --> 00:17:35,581
[gasps]

410
00:17:35,831 --> 00:17:37,713
[RED] Everyone's able
to laugh and celebrate now

411
00:17:37,793 --> 00:17:40,466
because of all the pain
you've endured to get us here.

412
00:17:42,048 --> 00:17:43,720
Now it's your turn to be happy.

413
00:17:44,391 --> 00:17:45,722
Only fair, don't you think?

414
00:17:47,184 --> 00:17:48,185
[RUTI] Thank you.

415
00:17:49,346 --> 00:17:50,347
Big brother.

416
00:17:52,770 --> 00:17:55,773
[wind whooshing]

417
00:17:59,778 --> 00:18:01,029
Would you like some wine?

418
00:18:01,320 --> 00:18:02,531
No. Thank you.

419
00:18:03,162 --> 00:18:05,164
-[wine gurgling]
-What's your assessment

420
00:18:05,284 --> 00:18:06,365
of our hero?

421
00:18:06,786 --> 00:18:09,248
Exceeding my expectations
in many ways.

422
00:18:09,869 --> 00:18:10,870
Is he now?

423
00:18:11,791 --> 00:18:14,544
Van's growth is proceeding
at a vastly rapid pace.

424
00:18:14,624 --> 00:18:16,587
The records you gave to me
prove as much.

425
00:18:17,087 --> 00:18:19,800
However, wouldn't that make
sending him to Zoltan

426
00:18:19,880 --> 00:18:21,973
a waste of time
when we could focus elsewhere?

427
00:18:22,974 --> 00:18:25,306
You speak as though
you've been to Zoltan yourself.

428
00:18:25,476 --> 00:18:27,308
A brief venture
with little gained.

429
00:18:27,979 --> 00:18:30,522
It has no economic
or historical significance.

430
00:18:30,942 --> 00:18:32,064
It's a dead end.

431
00:18:32,644 --> 00:18:34,897
Even if the demon lord's
airship is there,

432
00:18:35,898 --> 00:18:37,820
what purpose
would it serve for Van?

433
00:18:38,401 --> 00:18:40,363
An answer to ascertain, yes.

434
00:18:40,453 --> 00:18:42,205
Information is of the essence.

435
00:18:44,207 --> 00:18:45,999
Should the airship be found,

436
00:18:46,410 --> 00:18:49,123
both your assistance
and knowledge will be required.

437
00:18:53,047 --> 00:18:55,340
[LJUBO] I'm counting on you.
Don't forget that.

438
00:18:55,880 --> 00:18:56,881
Escarlata.

439
00:19:02,728 --> 00:19:04,600
The Festival went by so fast.

440
00:19:04,810 --> 00:19:06,432
Good thing it'll be back
next year.

441
00:19:07,023 --> 00:19:08,644
And will you be there with me?

442
00:19:09,315 --> 00:19:10,316
'Course I will.

443
00:19:11,187 --> 00:19:12,188
[RIT] And after that?

444
00:19:13,109 --> 00:19:14,110
Then, too.

445
00:19:14,361 --> 00:19:15,442
-[Rit giggles]
-[Red chuckles]

446
00:19:15,692 --> 00:19:20,077
♪

447
00:19:26,294 --> 00:19:27,295
Huh.

448
00:19:28,627 --> 00:19:30,879
[gasps] Is that for me?

449
00:19:31,340 --> 00:19:32,551
Go on, open it.

450
00:19:33,092 --> 00:19:34,093
Huh?

451
00:19:36,015 --> 00:19:37,136
Oh, Red.

452
00:19:37,807 --> 00:19:39,679
[RED] Well, you know,
I couldn't get you

453
00:19:39,769 --> 00:19:41,521
that blue sapphire
from the settlement,

454
00:19:42,222 --> 00:19:43,854
but this is my way
of promising you

455
00:19:43,934 --> 00:19:45,816
I'll get you that ring,
someday.

456
00:19:46,316 --> 00:19:48,939
[chuckles] You picked out
an engagement necklace?

457
00:19:49,109 --> 00:19:50,151
-Uh-huh.
-Hm.

458
00:19:50,781 --> 00:19:52,483
-Huh?
-[RIT] Can you?

459
00:19:53,114 --> 00:19:54,616
Oh. Yeah.

460
00:19:57,619 --> 00:20:00,662
♪

461
00:20:01,663 --> 00:20:02,875
Do you like it?

462
00:20:03,706 --> 00:20:05,458
[RED] Hmm. I love it.

463
00:20:06,419 --> 00:20:08,381
-You are beautiful.
-Huh.

464
00:20:10,673 --> 00:20:11,675
Oh!

465
00:20:14,177 --> 00:20:15,258
[RIT] No fair.

466
00:20:15,389 --> 00:20:16,390
What's wrong?

467
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:18,312
You pick out
a beautiful necklace

468
00:20:18,392 --> 00:20:19,393
for me to wear,

469
00:20:19,513 --> 00:20:21,515
then you tell me to wait
for a ring as well?

470
00:20:22,106 --> 00:20:24,319
I just...love you!

471
00:20:24,649 --> 00:20:25,690
Hm.

472
00:20:26,111 --> 00:20:28,113
I hope you know,
it's your fault for turning me

473
00:20:28,193 --> 00:20:29,614
into a hopeless romantic.

474
00:20:30,195 --> 00:20:31,577
You're not off the hook!

475
00:20:32,578 --> 00:20:33,579
How can I fix it?

476
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:35,331
Here's an idea.

477
00:20:37,243 --> 00:20:40,036
We will...sleep in together.

478
00:20:42,339 --> 00:20:43,670
And I'm the unfair one?

479
00:20:46,043 --> 00:20:50,678
♪

480
00:20:54,352 --> 00:20:56,725
[KAI] There's no information
about the airship anywhere.

481
00:20:57,606 --> 00:20:58,977
We need to turn up the heat.

482
00:20:59,688 --> 00:21:00,729
Lay low for now.

483
00:21:00,809 --> 00:21:03,312
It'll be much harder
to make a move otherwise.

484
00:21:03,943 --> 00:21:04,944
[KAI] Huh?

485
00:21:06,946 --> 00:21:08,618
Huh? Tisse!

486
00:21:09,158 --> 00:21:11,201
-Hm.
-Let's go! [grunts]

487
00:21:12,572 --> 00:21:13,663
[clanging]

488
00:21:13,744 --> 00:21:14,785
Go after them.

489
00:21:15,075 --> 00:21:16,497
-[squeaking]
-[Kai and Wolf panting]

490
00:21:17,828 --> 00:21:18,919
This is ridiculous.

491
00:21:18,999 --> 00:21:21,582
All that talk about laying low,
and then she pops in?

492
00:21:21,923 --> 00:21:23,925
I know something's up
in this town.

493
00:21:24,045 --> 00:21:25,176
[Kai grunts]

494
00:21:26,468 --> 00:21:27,679
[groaning]

495
00:21:27,929 --> 00:21:29,471
[KAI] What the heck
is all this?

496
00:21:29,641 --> 00:21:34,937
♪

497
00:21:35,097 --> 00:21:36,098
-Huh.
-Huh.

498
00:21:36,349 --> 00:21:39,352
♪

499
00:21:39,442 --> 00:21:40,483
Hm.

500
00:21:41,064 --> 00:21:42,566
Oh, crap. Huh?

501
00:21:42,776 --> 00:21:45,989
♪

502
00:21:46,110 --> 00:21:47,281
[gasps]

503
00:21:47,361 --> 00:21:48,702
[Kai and Wolf panting]

504
00:21:50,034 --> 00:21:51,035
[gasps]

505
00:21:51,245 --> 00:21:55,210
♪

506
00:21:55,460 --> 00:21:56,461
Are you...

507
00:21:58,463 --> 00:21:59,464
[grunts]

508
00:22:01,336 --> 00:22:02,338
[gasps]

509
00:22:02,428 --> 00:22:09,435
♪

